  "__instructions__": [
    "Replace this file with a real ComfyUI workflow JSON (API format).",
    "",
    "Model: FLUX.1-schnell (black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-schnell)",
    "Key difference from FLUX.1-dev: distilled model, 4-step inference, CFG=0.0.",
    "",
    "Steps:",
    "1. Open ComfyUI: http://localhost:8188",
    "2. ComfyUI Manager > Install Custom Nodes > search 'ComfyUI-FluxDev' (supports Schnell too)",
    "3. Manager > Model Manager > search 'FLUX.1-schnell' and install,",
    "   OR weights already at: comfy/ComfyUI/models/checkpoints/flux_schnell/",
    "4. Manager > Templates > find 'FLUX Schnell' (or load Flux template and adjust):",
    "   - KSampler: set steps=4, cfg=0.0, sampler_name='euler', scheduler='simple'",
    "   - FLUX.1-schnell does NOT use a negative prompt (distilled — leave it empty)",
    "   - Load checkpoint from flux_schnell/ folder",
    "5. Run a test prompt to verify output",
    "6. File > Save (API Format) -> save as workflows/flux_schnell_keyframe.json",
    "7. Delete this .stub file (or keep alongside as reference)",
    "",
    "Required input parameters (must be present in your workflow JSON):",
    "  - text prompt  (CLIPTextEncode positive node)",
    "  - width, height (EmptyLatentImage node)",
    "  - seed  (KSampler node)",
    "  - steps (KSampler — set to 4 for Schnell)",
    "  - cfg   (KSampler — set to 0.0 for Schnell; it is distilled and ignores CFG)",
    "",
    "Required output: SaveImage node with prefix 'flux_schnell_'",
    "",
    "Quality note: expect ~85% of FLUX.1-dev quality at ~7x the speed.",
    "For personal/research use where dev quality is needed, set COMMERCIAL_MODE=0.",
    "See docs/conventions.md 'License hygiene' for the dual-cascade policy."
  ]
